The Chronicle Sikhulekelani Moyo, Business Reporter ENVIRONMENT, Climate, Tourism and Hospitality Industry Minister  Nqobizitha Mangaliso Ndlovu today unveiled a new eight-member Zimbabwe Tourism Authority (ZTA) board. Last week, tourism expert Ms Winnie Muchanyuka was appointed as the new chief executive officer (CEO) for the tourism promotion body. On its Twitter handle, ZTA said three more board members will be announced in due course. The new board is chaired by Mr Ray Mawerera and deputised by  Dr Precious Sibiya. Other members include  Mrs Rita Likukuma, Mrs Veneranda Munyoro, Ms Beatrice Tonhodzayi, Mr Tare Munzara, Ms Precious Mazhande, Mr Admire Ndlovu, and Ms  Muchanyuka (Ex-Officio). -@SikhulekelaniM1